  "motivation": "Date has been a long-standing pain point in ECMAScript. This proposes Temporal, a global Object that acts as a top-level namespace (like Math), that brings a modern date/time API to the ECMAScript language. For a detailed breakdown of motivations, see: Fixing JavaScript Date https://maggiepint.com/2017/04/09/fixing-javascript-date-getting-started/",
  "devtrial_instructions": null,
  "activation_risks": "There are already polyfills and MDN docs out there. This library is designed to be directly usable by devs.",
  "measurement": null,
  "availability_expectation": null,
  "adoption_expectation": null,
  "adoption_plan": null,
  "initial_public_proposal_url": "https://github.com/tc39/proposal-temporal",
  "explainer_links": [
    "https://tc39.es/proposal-temporal/docs/",
    "https://tc39.es/proposal-temporal/"
  ],
  "requires_embedder_support": false,
  "spec_link": "https://tc39.es/proposal-temporal/",
  "api_spec": true,
  "automation_spec": false,
  "interop_compat_risks": "Temporal allows for calendar implementations to differ in specifics. All current implementors except for Safari use ICU4X for their non-ISO calendar implementations. Safari doesn't appear to support the non-ISO part of the spec yet.\n\nGenerally, this type of incompatability is expected behavior, and if not ICU4X, Safari's implementation would likely use ICU4C which is in alignment with ICU4X for modern dates.",
  "all_platforms": true,
  "all_platforms_descr": "This feature is supported on all platforms with Rust support, which includes all Chrome platforms.\n\nThere are some V8 platforms this is",
  "non_oss_deps": null,
  "anticipated_spec_changes": null,
  "security_risks": "This library calls into ICU4X, a Rust library, which might improve the safety of the code. However the (autogenerated, tested) FFI layer may have bugs. Overall it should not be much less secure than",
  "ergonomics_risks": "This will be used in tandem with the Date and Intl APIs.\n\nThere is no thread affinity for this API.",
  "wpt": true,
  "wpt_descr": "This is fully tested in test262.\n\nhttps://test262.fyi/#built-ins/Temporal\n\nNote that test262 shows a low percentage passing because of a bug in their infra (https://github.com/test262-fyi/data/pull/110). Locally we pass 99%.",
  "webview_risks": null,
